cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with geometric arrangements of polygons and their expansion, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of counting the number of blanks required involves combinatorial aspects, making categories such as cs.DS (data structures) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics) relevant. The use of tight bounds and analysis of the problem suggest categories such as cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.GT (computational geometry and topology) as well.
